title: Playoff picture still perfectly muddled
text:
Photo: Darron Cummings, Associated Press Ohio State’s Ezekiel Elliott had TD runs of 55, 65 and 75 yards. Ohio State’s Ezekiel Elliott had TD runs of 55, 65 and 75 yards.
The College Football Playoff has been around only a year, but there are two things the committee has gotten right. One, wait until November before ranking teams; two, treat the season in totality each week, not as an extension of the previous week. Ohio State’s Ezekiel Elliott had TD runs of 55, 65 and 75 yards.
